'''''Word Attack!''''' is a 1984 [[educational video game]] from [[Davidson & Associates]] for the [[Apple II]] and [[Atari 8-bit computers]]. An updated version was released as ''Word Attack! Plus.''

== Gameplay ==
The game consists of a series of language-based drill-and-practice [[minigame]]s and exercises. In one, the [[arrow keys]] tare used to fire at correct answer "targets". The nine programs are aimed at grades 4-12.

== Reception ==
By October 13, 1984, the game had sustained an 11-week streak on the [[Billboard charts|Billboard Charts]] for Top Educational Computer Software.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MiQEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PT26|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-10-13|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> It re-entered the charts on November 3, 1984 at #9,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wCQEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PA31|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-11-03|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> and again on November 24, 1984 at #7.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nyQEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PA25|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-11-24|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> By June 15, 1985, the game had stayed on the list for a total of 44 weeks, and was currently at #8.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-SQEAAAAMBAJ&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PT28|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1985-06-15|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>

''The Computer in Reading and Language Arts'' criticised the gameplay mechanic of shooting the correct [[multiple choice]] answers, finding the graphics out of place for an educational title.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CYZ4__pBowgC&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PA22|title=The Computer in Reading and Language Arts|last1=Blanchard|first1=Jay S.|last2=Mason|first2=George E.|date=1987-01-01|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=9780866566674|language=en}}</ref> ''[[InfoWorld]]'' deemed it well-[[Organization|organised]] and flexible, adding that it is an effective teaching tool.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ri8EAAAAMBAJ&q=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&pg=PA60|title=InfoWorld|last=Inc|first=InfoWorld Media Group|date=1983-10-17|publisher=InfoWorld Media Group, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>

